<h2>Which Dripper Should You Choose?</h2>

<div class="info-box">
  <h4>Decision Guide by Level and Goal</h4>
  <p>
    <strong>Complete beginner:</strong> Melitta (hardest to fail) or Kalita Wave (high consistency)<br />
    <strong>Intermediate — want to express origin character:</strong> Hario V60 (steep learning curve, highest ceiling)<br />
    <strong>Want to try both immersion and percolation styles:</strong> Hario Switch (one device, two modes)<br />
    <strong>Want versatility and to experiment:</strong> Origami Dripper (change cup character by changing filters)<br />
    <strong>Prioritize a clean, bright, transparent cup:</strong> Chemex (also functions as a beautiful serving carafe)<br />
    <strong>Café use, maximum consistency:</strong> Kalita Wave<br /><br />
    Budget note: start with a plastic V60 or entry-level Kalita to learn technique, then upgrade to ceramic or porcelain. More importantly, invest in a quality grinder before upgrading your dripper — grind uniformity has a greater impact on cup quality than the dripper choice.
  </p>
</div>

